editorialNotes.standard: Robust insights let you set goals and savour moments of mindfulness, uncovering more about your virtual pet’s personality, as well as your own needs too.

It’s hard to make the best even better, but the sequel to Day One lives up to expectations—and then some. The app keeps its interface streamlined but adds a wealth of new valuable features. Your journal entries contain all sorts of information—you can geolocate them, add tons of photos to each entry, and even see your day’s fitness activity. Switch over to the beautiful new photo view when you’re ready to see your world at a glance.
editorialNotes.short: Document your life with every entry.
Meditation programmes for all levels.
Learn how to make healthier choices about the food you eat.
Your background sounds for a quiet evening after a busy day.

editorialNotes.standard: Bookend your days with a moment of reflection in stoic., an elegantly designed journaling app made for anyone looking to carve out time for mindfulness. With insightful reflection prompts and breathing exercises, the app is filled with multiple ways to care for your mental health—with inspiration from stoic philosophy at its core.
editorialNotes.short: Meet your daily companion for journaling, meditation and reflection.

editorialNotes.standard: Take a deep breath: it’s both a call to action and a defining feature of this app’s approach to meditation. In a crowded field of mindfulness apps, it stands out for its ease of use and attention to (soothing) detail.
editorialNotes.short: Try breathing techniques for quick relaxation.

editorialNotes.standard: This is one of the few relaxation apps with an algorithm smart enough to customize soundscapes for you in the moment–from ocean waves to calming rain–whether you want to unwind, focus, or drift off to sleep.
editorialNotes.short: Calm down with personalised soundscapes.
Achieve your fitness and wellness goals.

editorialNotes.standard: An invaluable tool for reaching your weight-loss goals, Lose It! tracks your meals, exercise, and nutrition. Documenting food is effortless with its built-in barcode scanner, searchable list of common grocery items, and database of popular restaurant meals’ nutritional facts. Plus, when you need some extra motivation, the app’s social features make it easy to find inspiration from friends and cheer each other on.
editorialNotes.short: Stay on track and monitor your daily calorie budget.

editorialNotes.standard: This app started as a simple timer app for meditating, but it’s evolved into a comprehensive way to help people, while gaining insight along the way. With lessons which range from short to long and luxurious, it features thousands of guided meditations across a range of styles.
editorialNotes.short: Set a timer or relax with guided meditation sessions.

editorialNotes.standard: Making a pledge to get fit is easy, but finding the time to actually move our bodies is hard. Seven’s bite-size workouts don’t require a gym membership or special equipment. Best of all, we can launch these satisfying mini-routines right from Apple Watch—it’s like having a rah-rah personal trainer right on our wrist.
editorialNotes.short: Bite-size workouts to help you smash your goals.

editorialNotes.standard: Track your sleep, record your moods and meals (and caffeine intake), and follow your daily routine with the app that’s stuffed with ways to improve your slumber, night after night.
editorialNotes.short: Measure your sleep quality accurately and improve your routine.

editorialNotes.tagline: Join a live class from home
editorialNotes.standard: Each on-demand class is a community affair with others cheering you on. Encouraging coaches and detailed stats help you stay consistent in maintaining your streak.

Want to break a sweat? Celebrity trainers like actor Gabrielle Union and Queer Eye guru Jonathan Van Ness guide you through challenging routines you can stream on demand, while FitOn’s core fitness team leads live classes nearly every hour of the day.

If you’re like us, you need all the help you can get turning rare quiet moments into true meditation. Headspace’s rich, accessible lessons gently explore how to improve mindfulness. Oh, and we love how Headspace’s Apple Watch app lets you hit a literal panic button when extra-stressful situations arise.
editorialNotes.short: Stay relaxed during busy times.

editorialNotes.standard: Rather than yanking you from your slumber like an alarm clock, this app analyzes your sleep patterns using your device’s microphone, then picks your lightest sleep to rouse you gently.
editorialNotes.short: Keep track of your sleeping habits and wake up feeling rested.

editorialNotes.standard: Fitness expert Kayla Itsines wants you to reach all your health and exercise goals–and her app has just what you need to get there, from workouts and meal plans to programmes for weights, yoga, and post-pregnancy.
editorialNotes.short: Try short 28-minute workouts, with a 7-day free trial.

editorialNotes.standard: There’s nothing like a cute llama to help you track the liquids you consume. As you do, unlock a world of characters, tools, and challenges to help you stay on top of your hydration goals.

editorialNotes.short: Work out at home with a smart exercise plan.

editorialNotes.standard: With detailed plans (including nutrition and cross-training advice), Runna makes an excellent, pocket-size running coach. Lean on the app’s coaches and AI-powered features to help you find your stride, connect with fellow runners, and smash your race-day goals.
